                    "text": "Incident packet assembled—start quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-1",
            "text": "Which command follows new lines from a live log file in real time?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "tail -f /var/log/syslog"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-1",
                    "text": "df -h"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-1",
                    "text": "uname -a"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-1",
            "text": "Use `tail -f` when you need continuous updates as events arrive.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Retry"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-2",
            "text": "What is the most focused way to inspect one systemd service's logs?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "journalctl -u my-service"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-2",
                    "text": "ls /etc"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-2",
                    "text": "pwd"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-2",
            "text": "`journalctl -u <service>` scopes logs to one unit and cuts noise.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "Retry"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-3",
            "text": "Why save extracted logs into an artifact file before escalating?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "It creates reproducible evidence teammates can review asynchronously"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-3",
                    "text": "Because journalctl cannot display plain text"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-3",
                    "text": "Because tail deletes old lines"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-3",
            "text": "Artifact files help handoff and postmortems; they are about collaboration, not command limitations.",
